 jeezy petes. Who'da thought that a throwaway creepypasta about a 2spooky statue who breaks people's necks in a puddle of blood and poop would eventually give rise to something this high-brow? Look how far we've come, everyone. God damn.

So, let me preface the rest of my comment with an admission that this is a clever, marvellous, clever, clever piece of writing. What an idea! What an execution! As Mr Eldritch has done a fine job of explaining(/spoiling!) to us. But

If anything, it's stupidly clever. And this is where my personal bias comes in. My own writing philosophy is quite unashamedly populist, and what you've written here is so damn smart that ninety-plus per cent of people are simply not going to get it at all. This thing is flying so far above most people's heads, it's not even in Earth orbit.

As was obvious from your casual use of the word , I can tell that you don't give two hoots about some people not getting it. And I won't for one second judge you. I would never say that every single piece of media needs to have mass appeal in order to be good.

But you shouldn't be surprised if this doesn't break +100. In quality of the idea, and of the writing, and the hook, this blows most of the Top Rated Pages out of the water. But you've erected a big intellectual barrier to understanding this that not many readers will be able to climb.

However: +1 from me, with no hesitation

