Let me preface this by pointing out that I was asked and wanted to critique this in its earlier stages, but did and could not.

There are more narratives that can be constructed from this one, thanks to the rampant numerology. It's a metanarrative to a concept that reaches through the first six to find the seventh tantalizingly out of reach just yet.

Furthermore, the constant theme of effort resulting in never reaching the goal, an outpouring of toil leading to no actual progress Let's just say that it's been a recurring theme in some of my works.

The infinite asypmtotic approach to finality, the singularity that you can get ever closer to, yet never precisely reach. The fractal spiral.

Where have we seen these before? In many places, throughout the wiki.

That is the (trembling) core of the awakening.

